Description: Fragment of oval handle of a probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 3. Not a known stamp or name.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1506)
